## ✨ Features

### 📚 Complete Subject Coverage
- 12 subjects with detailed micro-syllabus
- Standard books with purchase links
- YouTube playlists curated by subject
- Previous year questions (2015-2024)

### 🔗 500+ Curated Resources
- Official government websites
- Educational platforms and YouTube channels
- Free PDFs and study materials
- Advanced filtering and search

### 🏆 Topper Strategies
- 10 toppers (AIR 1-10) with complete strategies
- Prelims, Mains, Optional, Interview breakdowns
- Blogs, interviews, and notes links

### 📰 Daily Current Affairs
- 50+ entries with smart tagging
- Prelims and Mains relevance
- Facts to remember
- Auto-linking to glossary

### 🧠 Interactive Quiz
- 60+ questions across all subjects
- Timed quizzes with explanations
- Progress tracking and streaks
- Performance analytics

### 📅 Study Planner
- Drag-drop weekly calendar
- Pre-built templates for all stages
- Progress tracking
- Export and print support

### 📖 120+ Term Glossary
- Searchable dictionary of UPSC terms
- Hindi translations
- Related terms and examples
- Bookmark and flashcard mode

### 🧮 Score Calculator
- Prelims, Mains, Interview calculators
- Attempts left calculator
- Previous year cutoff comparison
- Rank prediction

### ✍️ Answer Writing Practice
- Mains answer writing tool
- Self-review checklist
- Model answer comparison
- Progress tracking

### 📚 NCERT Library
- Class 6-12 all subjects
- Download links
- Reading progress tracking

### 🎤 Interview Preparation
- DAF analysis guide
- Mock interview resources
- Common questions
- Dress code and etiquette

### 💪 Motivation Center
- Daily quotes and affirmations
- Success stories
- Topper interviews
- Progress celebrations

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 15 (App Router)
- **Language:** TypeScript 5.3+ (Strict Mode)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS 3.4+
- **UI Components:** Shadcn/ui
- **Animation:** Framer Motion
- **Charts:** Recharts
- **Drag & Drop:** @dnd-kit
- **PDF Export:** html2canvas + jspdf

## 🚀 Quick Start

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourname/upsc-cse-hub.git

# Navigate to project
cd upsc-cse-hub

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Run development server
npm run dev
